tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mild hypoglycemia, elevated creatinine suggesting impaired renal function, and significant proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria, indicating possible nephropathy and metabolic derangement. Urine is brown, cloudy, and has low specific gravity, further supporting renal involvement. No evidence of urinary tract infection. HbA1c is low-normal, arguing against chronic hyperglycemia. Recommend urgent clinical evaluation for acute or chronic kidney disease and possible metabolic or prerenal causes.
